# pi-ai-go example configuration
#
# Copy this file to `.env` next to the example binary and edit it
# in place. The example calls loadDotEnv on every run; entries are
# only set when the corresponding env var is not already present in
# the process environment, so real env vars always win.

# --- Model selection ---------------------------------------------------
# Model ID (see resolveModel in main.go for the hard-coded map). The
# provider / base URL are auto-derived from this value; override with
# PROVIDER / BASE_URL below.
#
# Default if unset: gpt-4o
MODEL=gpt-4o

# Provider id (openai, anthropic, deepseek, glm, kimi, ...). Empty =
# auto-detect from the model ID. Default: ""
PROVIDER=

# Provider base URL. Empty = use the model ID's default. Default: ""
# Useful for proxies or self-hosted endpoints, e.g.:
#   BASE_URL=https://my-proxy.example.com/v1
BASE_URL=

# --- API key -----------------------------------------------------------
# Generic key (preferred). If empty, the example falls back to the
# provider's standard env var alias (OPENAI_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY,
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY, ZAI_API_KEY / GLM_API_KEY, KIMI_API_KEY / ...).
# API_KEY=

# Per-provider keys (picked up via core.ResolveAPIKey).
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...
# DEEPSEEK_API_KEY=sk-...
# ZAI_API_KEY=...
# GLM_API_KEY=...
# KIMI_API_KEY=...
# MOONSHOT_API_KEY=...
# XIAOMI_API_KEY=...

# --- Skills -----------------------------------------------------------
# Directory containing SKILL.md files. Override with -skills flag or
# by setting this variable. Default: "" (no skills loaded).
# SKILLS=./skills
